				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Valarm, even easier is to use the following:
<br />
<ul>/ma "Cure" &lt;p#&gt;
<br />
#=character placement in party list. (i.e.  I'm normally party leader, <span style="font-style: italic">for some reason</span>, so my name is at the top and my # is 0 and my friend Arkose is next on the list and therefore has a # of 1.)</ul>
<br />
Here are a couple of my macros I use.
<br />
CTRL+1:  /ma "Cure" &lt;me&gt;
<br />
CTRL+2:  /ma "Cure" &lt;p1&gt;
<br />
CTRL+6:  /ma "Paralyze" &lt;t&gt;
<br />
               /wait 6
<br />
               /ma "Banish" &lt;t&gt;
<br />

<br />
I always use &lt;me&gt; instead of &lt;p0&gt; so I always know I'll be healing myself.
<br />
Hope this speeds things up for you as it has allowed me to save party member's lives time and again.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
