				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Allow me to recommend something, instead of using the target tag, &lt;t&gt;, use the tag, &lt;bt&gt;.  &lt;bt&gt; will ALWAYS AUTOMATICALLY target the spell on the mob that the group is fighting.
<br />
This makes for a MUCH less stressful and less dangerous situation when casting debuffs or damage spells on your party's mobs as you know that you won't be casting on the wrong one.
<br />
One warning: if the group has "claimed" two mobs, it will cast on the mob CLOSEST to you so be careful.
<br />
I've used this tag for the last two weeks at least and have never once accidently casted a spell on a mob we weren't fighting.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row1" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
